.TH "pekwm" "1" "0.1.3" "Claes Nasten" "Window Manager"
.SH "NAME"
.LP 
pekwm \- A Small, Fast window manager
.SH "FULL DOCUMENTATION"
.LP 
The full documentation for pekwm is distributed in html format: You can find it at http://pekwm.org/documentation.php. We also distribute a copy in the docs/ subdirectory of the source distribution.
.SH "SYNTAX"
.LP 
pekwm [\fIoption\fP]
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.LP 
The pekwm window manager is a small, fast, and light window manager which supports xinerama, grouping multiple windows in a single frame, has pixmap themes, a keygrapper that supports keyhains, redefinable key and mouse bindings, and much more.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.LP 
.TP 
\fB\-\-display\fR display.
Specifies which X display to use
.TP 
\fB\-\-help\fR
Output help information and exit.
.TP 
\fB\-\-version\fR
Output version information and exit.
.TP 
\fB\-\-info\fR
Show extended info to be used on bug reports and exit.
.SH "FILES"
.LP 
\fI${HOME}/.pekwm\fP 
Directory of per\-user config files and themes.
.br 
\fI<PREFIX>/share\fP 
Contains the default files for everything above.
.SH "ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES"
.LP 
.TP 
\fBHOME\fP
pekwm looks here for config files
.SH "AUTHORS"
.LP 
